{
  "stem": "26111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What I saw was the next day, in the street.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was something that, that was very, very hard to, to see.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was harder for the people who was-- whose shops and whose-- there was-- I saw one piano that had been thrown out of the window of a-- of a Jewish apartment owner.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and it was lying there, on the street, a Bechstein.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] No, no, it was not an adventure.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was fear from beginning to end.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was fear of, as I mentioned before, being harmed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think I mentioned it in the context of being a child in Konigsberg.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Being an adolescent in Berlin was worse because I was an adolescent, and I was half child, half man.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was therefore-- you beat up a child, it's a little bit less easy than beating up a young man.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the older I got, the more I realized I was vulnerable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Secondly, when you were out on the street, you had to keep a very careful eye out for people who either knew you, knew of you-- doesn't mean only the famous people.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, people from the neighborhood or whatever-- that have some idea, tradespeople, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they talk an awful lot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And if they're party members and they-- oh, there goes the Jew, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But worst of all was in Berlin-- I didn't get this in Konigsberg.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't think they were organized yet that way.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
